{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place a large bowl onto mixing bowl lid and weigh tomatoes into it. Remove tomato skins by using a sharp knife to cut a small cross in base of each tomato. Carefully pour boiling water into bowl to cover tomatoes. Leave until skins split (approx. 1 minute). Remove from water and once cool enough to touch, peel away skins, then cut flesh into quarters. Set tomatoes aside.","Place Parmesan into mixing bowl and grate <b>15 sec\/speed 8<b>. Transfer into a small bowl and set aside.","Place cheddar into mixing bowl and grate <b>6 sec\/speed 7<b>. Transfer into a large bowl and set aside.","Place cauliflower into mixing bowl and grate <b>2 sec\/speed 6<b>. Transfer into bowl with cheddar and set aside.","Place onion and garlic into mixing bowl and chop <b>4 sec\/speed 6<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add oil and cook <b>3 min\/100°C\/\/speed 1<b>.","Add rice and cook <b>2 min\/100°C\/\/speed 1<b>.","Add reserved tomatoes, liquid stock, then cook <b>12 min\/90°C\/\/speed 1.5<b>.","Add reserved cheddar and cauliflower and half of the reserved Parmesan, then stir through with aid of spatula. Cook <b>9 min\/90°C\/\/speed 1.5<b> or until rice is tender. Allow to cool slightly, then serve topped with remaining Parmesan."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["boiling water","300 g ripe tomatoes","80 g Parmesan cheese, cut into pieces (3 cm)","80 g cheddar cheese, cut into pieces (3 cm)","200 g cauliflower, cut into florets","1 brown onion, cut into quarters","1 garlic clove","20 g extra virgin olive oil","150 g arborio rice","200 g liquid vegetable stock (see Tips)"]}],"id":"r404348","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-PARjs5Y74Bg\/XZMyOqE85JI\/AAAAAAAAaiM\/D-xaS_MHgzEDb7N99AG7syocgUoKcHDYACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_7P5PTz5l1YsD_uwH.png","title":"Cheesy tomato risotto","publishedAt":"2019-05-06T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"16.2 g","fat":"16.3 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"34.3 g","calories":"1504.8 kJ \/ 358.3 kcal"},"usefulItems":"small bowl, large bowl","hintsAndTricks":["You can replace liquid vegetable stock with Vegetable stock paste and water in this recipe. Please refer to <i>The Basic Cookbook<\/i> for the Vegetable stock paste recipe. In step 8 replace liquid stock with 2 teaspoons Vegetable stock paste and 200 g water.","Adding hidden cauliflower to risotto is a great way to give your child an extra serve of vegetable and a nutrient boost. You might also like to serve some 'visible' steamed cauliflower on the side so that your child becomes accustomed to seeing and tasting cauliflower on its own too."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","40m","4 portions"]}